    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1730415382" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1730415382" />
    <a title="Choko" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27962805-choko"><img alt="Choko" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1475642755p2/27962805.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1730415382?book_show_action=true">Aug 16, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Choko" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Choko" href="/user/show/27962805-choko">Choko</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789546554840" href="/book/show/21941789">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27962805-choko?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27962805-choko?shelf=advanture">advanture</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27962805-choko?shelf=brent-weeks">brent-weeks</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1730415382" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5077332725418074736"><b>*** 4.85 ***<br/><br/>A buddy read with Eon and Sarah La Luna @ the Mecca for Fantasy on GR, BB&amp;B!!! </b><br/><br/>Epic! Not just the genre of Fantasy, but the book itself - EPIC!!! Brent Weeks has taken the torch of Epic Fantasy with some traditional leanings and is finding his way into our hearts and Favorites Book Shelves.... I am in awe of the magical system BW has chosen to base this World on and am fascinated by the different cultures and how their ethnological and physical differences are conducive to one aspect</span>
  <span id="freeText5077332725418074736" style="display:none"><b>*** 4.85 ***<br /><br />A buddy read with Eon and Sarah La Luna @ the Mecca for Fantasy on GR, BB&amp;B!!! </b><br /><br />Epic! Not just the genre of Fantasy, but the book itself - EPIC!!! Brent Weeks has taken the torch of Epic Fantasy with some traditional leanings and is finding his way into our hearts and Favorites Book Shelves.... I am in awe of the magical system BW has chosen to base this World on and am fascinated by the different cultures and how their ethnological and physical differences are conducive to one aspect of the magic or another.... One thing is obvious - Brent Weeks is setting up the stage for a grand adventure, a story for the ages, a major battle of Good, Evil, and all those many hews in between... <br /><br />Chromeria. It is the land of 7 Satrupies/States, governed by satrups, all under the umbrella of Chromeria and its ruling body of 7 Colors drafters, a Black, a White, and the highest placed, kind of like an Emperor - The Prism. At this time The Prism is Gavin Guile and he can draft all the Colors in the rainbow. You see, in this world the magic is based on light and the way it makes the eye perceive it and then translate it into colors. Those who have been born with the ability to take in the light of any color and pull it into their body cells, then learn how to shape the byproduct, luxin, into some useful form, those are the Drafters, the magicians of their world. They are blessed, live well, fast, and early on succumb to madness and death... Everyone knows the score, the whole system has been shaped to accommodate those limitations. Each generation there is only one Prism born, the person who brings balance to the Color-system Magic and the defacto Pope and Emperor... Or at least, there SHOULD be only one, until Gavin and his brother, Dazen Guile. And with them came the War of the Prisms.... <br /><br />The magic system is intricate and complex, but it is amazing, especially once you get used to the character of the different colors and the way the magic can be drafted and utilized. The characters are introduced as the action builds and by the end, when things are hectic and nerve wracking, we know and already root for the ones we get to know best - Gavin, the lady he is crazy about Karris, and Kip, the chubby, hormone riddled, clumsy, awkward, and extremely inappropriate teenager with a Haze addict for a mother, and a father he just learns about, who is lost, has lost everything he has known, and now is absolutely confused as to what he is supposed to do, learn or be from now on.... Yes, Kip is the typical young man of the Classical Fantasy Genre, on his requisite journey to discover himself and fight to be as good as he can be, while fighting temptation and the darkness within. It is a cliche, yes, but it is THE cliche we keep coming back for time and again, craving for one more time, at least in Fantasy, for the good guys to learn their lessons and come back on top. This is why we read this genre, isn't it??? <br /><br /><i>
  <b>"... Kip had made his oaths to the living and to the dead. He gritted his teeth, sure he was making the wrong decision—and making it anyway. It’s better that the innocent should live than that the guilty die....</b>
</i><br /><br />It is all about choices, guilt, and secrets. It is GLORIOUS! <br /><br />I will recommend this to all the Fantasy fans. The beginning is a bit slow, until you get used to the complex magic system, but after that it is all easy sailing, so don't give up on it, it is sooooo worth it! And as a person who has had extensive color theory at school, I can only say that if such drafting was possible, this would be as close to the characteristics of the colors as it could get! Fascinating, engaging and filled with action - what more can you ask for???<br /><br />I wish you all Happy Reading and may you never stop believing in the fantastical!!!! </span>
  <a data-text-id="5077332725418074736" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


