    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3159692452" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3159692452" />
    <a title="Brenda Waworga" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62212312-brenda-waworga"><img alt="Brenda Waworga" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1507467774p2/62212312.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3159692452?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brenda Waworga" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brenda Waworga" href="/user/show/62212312-brenda-waworga">Brenda Waworga</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780316246279" href="/book/show/16131107-the-black-prism">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3159692452" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16981842503367025305">I swear i never read an epic Fantasy book centered so much on <b>PHYSICAL TRAITS</b> like i read on this book (example: breast and fat got mention so many times) <br/><br/>Now start with things I love from this book… I really love the magic system, it reminds me a lot with “WARBREAKER” by Brandon Sanderson (which i really love) but with so much more details, people have the ability to get power from colors, those colors also can produce certain shape and smell and have unique characterizations, it took me a long</span>
  <span id="freeText16981842503367025305" style="display:none">I swear i never read an epic Fantasy book centered so much on <b>PHYSICAL TRAITS</b> like i read on this book (example: breast and fat got mention so many times) <br /><br />Now start with things I love from this book… I really love the magic system, it reminds me a lot with “WARBREAKER” by Brandon Sanderson (which i really love) but with so much more details, people have the ability to get power from colors, those colors also can produce certain shape and smell and have unique characterizations, it took me a long time to understand it because it was just so complex! It also felt infodumpy , you need to learn and remember a lot of things on the first 300 pages. I also love the idea about the worldbuilding (Seven Satrapies surround The Cerulean Sea) and The Chromeria.<br /><br />Now onto the things I really REALLY DISLIKE… the way the author described and treated FEMALE CHARACTERS, THEY MAKE ME <b>CRINGE SO.MANY.TIMES</b>, I can handle some sexist/sexualized lines in fantasy book.. but there are just too many in this book, they really kill my enjoyment to read the story. <br /><br />I also don't like any of the character in this book, Gavin did so many horrible decisions and i just cannot root for him, Kip is a teenager with raging hormones, Karris describes as a badass female character but all she did is whinny about her ex from 15 years ago and when she got important mission, she got caught, Liv is another useless bland a bit dumb female character <br /><br />Sad I don’t like this book as much as I wanted to .. some of my friends said, the author's style didn’t change much through the series about the way he describe and treat women, so I guess I will just stop here and not continue read this series<br /><br /><b>2.5⭐️</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="16981842503367025305" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


